/// kernel can't tell whether it's hitting a cache or the underlying
/// source. Mirrors Haskell's `lmdbCachedEdgeLookup` from
/// `lmdb_fact_source.hs.mustache`.
///
/// Implementation: sharded `Mutex<HashMap>` with per-shard FIFO
/// eviction once `cap_per_shard` is reached. FIFO (rather than LRU)
/// keeps the hot path lock-free of LRU bookkeeping; for our
/// read-only graph workload the value-correctness contract is
/// preserved either way (any miss falls through to the inner source).
///
/// Atom-side methods (`lookup_key_for_atom`, `atom_for_key`) are
/// passthrough — only `lookup_parents` is cached, which is the
/// expensive cursor-seek operation.
